# P99 Classic-Era Mechanics

This project targets **Project 1999** (P99), a classic EverQuest emulator locked to the **Velious expansion** (circa 1999–2001). Many mechanics differ from later expansions and live EQ. Always verify assumptions against https://wiki.project1999.com/ rather than general EQ knowledge.

## Stat Mechanics (from P99 wiki Statistics page)

### AGI — Nearly worthless above 75
Above 75 AGI, each 10 points gives only ~3 AC. Below 75 causes a severe penalty (45 AC loss for 10 points). There is NO special Monk AGI formula. The Monk wiki says the impact is "generally agreed to be small." Treat AGI as a threshold stat (need 75), not a scaling stat.

### DEX — Procs and class-specific crits only
- **All melee**: weapon proc rate (the only universal benefit)
- **Warriors ONLY**: small influence on melee weapon crit chance
- **Rangers ONLY**: small influence on bow crit rate
- **Rogues ONLY**: small influence on THROWN weapon crits (NOT backstab crits)
- **Bards ONLY**: reduces song fizzle (missed notes)
- DEX does NOT affect backstab crits, melee crits for non-Warriors, or hit rate in PvE

### STR — Primary DPS stat for all melee
Directly increases ATK which increases max and average melee damage including backstab and flying kick. Every melee class wiki recommends STR as the primary DPS stat allocation.

### STA — Tanks benefit significantly, others less so
The wiki states: "Only tanks gain significantly from this stat, Warriors, Shadowknights and Paladins." HP per STA scales with level and is much higher for tank classes.

### WIS/INT — Soft cap at 200
Below 200: ~11.3 mana per point at level 60. Above 200: ~5.6 mana per point (half value).

### CHA — Enchanter/Bard only for combat
Affects charm duration, mez resist rate, lull critical fail rate, memory blur success for ENC/BRD only. Does NOT affect Druid or Necromancer charm. Vendor price impact caps at 104-132 CHA.

## Class Stat Priorities (from wiki allocation recommendations)

- **Warrior**: STA (dump all), DEX is their unique crit stat
- **Rogue**: STR 25 / STA 5 (grouping); STR is backstab damage, DEX is procs only
- **Monk**: STR (DPS) or STA (pulling/raid); AGI and DEX are both minor
- **Ranger**: STR (DPS) or STA (raid); WIS for mana; DEX is minor
- **Bard**: STA 25; CHA for charm/lull/mez; DEX for song fizzle
- **Paladin**: STA (dump all after 75 AGI); WIS for spells; DEX for proc weapons
- **Shadow Knight**: STA or STR+INT split; INT for lifetaps/FD
- **Enchanter**: CHA 25 (all modes); CHA is #1 recommended stat, INT secondary
- **Shaman**: STA + WIS split; HP > mana due to Cannibalize
- **Cleric/Druid**: WIS dominant
- **Wizard/Mage/Necro**: INT dominant
